resolution: "Updated pm CLI/SDK and pm-changelog to 2026.7.10, TypeScript to 7.0.2, Node types to 26.1.1, checkout to v7, aligned manifest/peer minimums, stopped tracking generated dist while retaining package builds, and made changelog verification preserve accurate legacy sections across rewritten history."
expected_result: "Current contracts, warning-free importer/exporter activation, reproducible release checks, generated package artifacts, and no loss of valid changelog history."
actual_result: "All 90 tests, typecheck, production audit, package dry-run, and real installed doctor passed; package exposes native importer/exporter and commands without warnings; legacy tag ancestry was handled with prepend-window validation."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-11T00:48:36.565Z",codex,"After repository history rewrites, full changelog regeneration cannot reconstruct releases whose tags are no longer ancestors. Validate and generate the next release with the same since-previous-tag prepend window so authoritative historical sections remain intact."
